WEBVTT

00:00.002 --> 00:00.963
Okay, thank you, Sung.

00:01.584 --> 00:02.665
Well, good morning, everyone.

00:03.686 --> 00:05.467
Happy first month of 2026.

00:05.527 --> 00:09.411
It's off to a fast start, isn't it?

00:10.652 --> 00:21.262
And as we're at the start of the new year, we are so grateful for the mercy of God, and that's what I want us to sing about today.

00:21.322 --> 00:24.646
He's brought us into another year, and we're grateful for that.

00:24.666 --> 00:29.330
He sustains us, and he upholds us, and he provides for us

00:29.986 --> 00:43.405
Ephesians 2 verse 4 tells us, but God who is rich in mercy because of the great love with which he loved us, even when we were dead in our trespasses, made us alive together with Christ.

00:44.427 --> 00:46.390
Our God is rich in mercy.

00:46.410 --> 00:47.071
Isn't that great?

00:48.172 --> 00:49.274
He has an endless supply.

00:50.295 --> 00:54.922
And the definitive act of mercy took place at Calvary.

00:55.523 --> 00:57.586
Mercy there was great.

00:57.826 --> 00:59.008
and grace was free.

00:59.069 --> 01:01.854
Part in there was multiplied to me.

01:02.676 --> 01:06.925
There my burdened soul found liberty at Calvary.

01:06.965 --> 01:11.314
Let's open our service, singing this great hymn of the faith together.

01:35.138 --> 01:35.667
me.

05:00.706 --> 05:01.567
for that mercy.

05:04.812 --> 05:06.614
We find His mercy undeserved.

05:08.497 --> 05:10.339
We find His mercy abundant.

05:11.621 --> 05:12.762
We find it matchless.

05:13.664 --> 05:16.868
And this next hymn reminds us that we find it infinite.

05:16.988 --> 05:17.829
It never ends.

05:18.710 --> 05:30.226
Redeemed, how I love to proclaim it, redeemed by the blood of the Lamb, redeemed through His infinite mercy, His child, and forever.

05:30.818 --> 05:32.179
I am singing it together.

08:41.698 --> 08:43.801
so thankful for that infinite mercy.

08:44.302 --> 08:47.086
It's a well that never runs dry.

08:48.308 --> 08:52.955
We don't have to wait for a new year for the Lord to replenish His mercy to us.

08:52.975 --> 08:54.878
We don't have to wait for a new calendar month.

08:54.938 --> 08:58.804
His mercies are renewed every day of our lives.

08:59.825 --> 09:07.717
Lamentations 3.22 to 23 reminds us, the steadfast love of the Lord never ceases.

09:08.378 --> 09:11.122
His mercies never come to an end.

09:11.618 --> 09:13.505
They are new every morning.

09:14.409 --> 09:15.875
Great is your faithfulness.

09:16.818 --> 09:21.938
Let's close our singing with those words, the steadfast love of our Lord.

13:18.754 --> 13:19.835
Thank you, worship team.

13:20.977 --> 13:23.260
Beautiful songs.

13:23.280 --> 13:25.342
Our Lord deserves those songs, doesn't he?

13:31.771 --> 13:33.513
Good morning or good afternoon, everyone.

13:34.514 --> 13:37.338
Let's commit this time to the Lord Heavenly Father.

13:39.080 --> 13:44.327
Lord, thank you for this time, this day, or we could just worship you.

13:44.627 --> 13:47.090
Lord, you deserve all the thanks.

13:47.234 --> 13:49.136
and the worship that we have in our hearts.

13:50.918 --> 13:56.284
Where we could just put aside a little time of our week and give it all to you.

13:57.846 --> 14:00.549
Lord, I dedicate this message to you.

14:02.911 --> 14:05.074
Put me where I belong right now.

14:06.235 --> 14:06.755
Humble me.

14:11.020 --> 14:12.121
You're the one up here.

14:14.364 --> 14:15.225
Use my body.

14:15.425 --> 14:16.466
Use my voice.

14:17.026 --> 14:20.150
to speak whatever you want to say, Lord, to the congregation.

14:21.471 --> 14:30.382
And Lord, I just pray that this message would pierce through hearts today and that we would be able to use it.

14:32.024 --> 14:34.628
We give you glory, Lord, not me.

14:35.569 --> 14:36.610
It's not about me today.

14:36.910 --> 14:37.531
It's about you.

14:38.052 --> 14:39.734
We love you in Jesus' name, amen.

14:45.261 --> 14:46.322
Be still.

14:47.298 --> 14:48.840
and know that I'm God.

14:51.625 --> 14:56.332
Be still and know that I'm God one more time.

14:58.335 --> 15:01.960
Be still and know that I'm God.

15:02.842 --> 15:13.458
Psalms 46-10, it's been proven that to remember something, it generally takes a minimum of three repetitions

15:13.922 --> 15:17.207
for the average person to recall the information effectively.

15:19.029 --> 15:19.730
And that's what I did.

15:21.252 --> 15:24.397
Now, I know we had this same topic a few months ago.

15:25.138 --> 15:31.887
A brother Randy touched on this subject on his beautiful sermon about the master of the wind.

15:31.947 --> 15:35.592
And believe me, I went back and forth with the Lord on this one.

15:35.652 --> 15:37.214
I said, Lord, pick me another subject.

15:37.275 --> 15:40.439
I can't because we've already talked about this.

15:40.459 --> 15:42.642
And he said, no, you're going to talk about this one.

15:45.666 --> 15:49.390
And don't be like me.

15:50.231 --> 15:52.194
I tried to push this to somebody else.

15:52.694 --> 15:53.415
I said, you know what?

15:53.455 --> 15:55.518
Lord, this message would be good for this person.

15:56.439 --> 16:00.224
Not knowing that I needed it badly this week.

16:02.767 --> 16:07.713
I was having a tough time and stressful time at work, and so I needed it.

16:08.814 --> 16:15.602
And when the doctor mentioned it this morning, it was like the Lord, this is the subject I want you to talk about.

16:16.994 --> 16:18.956
Treat it like a constant reminder.

16:19.918 --> 16:28.768
Remember, your parents used to give you constant reminders, like, stand up straight, chew your food.

16:29.569 --> 16:33.354
My mom used to tell me, Alan, slow down in eating.

16:33.594 --> 16:34.696
We're not going to run out of food.

16:36.878 --> 16:45.048
And then for my spiritual parents, Sally used to tell me, it's not always about you, Alan.

16:45.689 --> 16:46.450
Rick knows this.

16:47.522 --> 16:51.448
Another thing she used to say, and I have to do it the right way.

16:51.468 --> 16:54.152
Did you pray, hun?

16:56.496 --> 17:01.203
And I would say, Sally, you don't understand, but yes, I haven't prayed.

17:01.243 --> 17:03.506
I'm going to go back to reading my word.

17:05.209 --> 17:07.953
Sylvia used to tell me a lot.

17:09.055 --> 17:09.495
Love them.

17:11.138 --> 17:11.919
Love them anyway.

17:13.341 --> 17:14.883
Or keep moving.

17:15.584 --> 17:16.626
Press forward, Alan.

17:18.210 --> 17:20.173
Bill, Bill was one of the best.

17:20.754 --> 17:24.159
Watch the dude, meaning watch your attitude.

17:24.940 --> 17:26.362
He knew when I was grumpy.

17:30.408 --> 17:35.716
And then there's sayings that we've heard, God will honor those who honor me.

17:36.757 --> 17:36.998
Right?

17:38.560 --> 17:39.141
We've heard that.

17:39.642 --> 17:41.484
Who's heard that one?

17:41.504 --> 17:41.685
Right?

17:42.386 --> 17:43.447
We know who that person is.

17:44.068 --> 17:48.114
And if it weren't for his other saying, I'd probably be late to church.

17:49.282 --> 17:51.244
I will see you Sunday bright end.

17:52.766 --> 17:53.828
Oh, you've heard it before.

17:53.888 --> 17:59.895
We're going to go through Exodus.

18:01.978 --> 18:11.109
Exodus chapter 14 tells us of the famous crossing of the Red Sea, a well-known story we've heard since Sunday school.

18:12.391 --> 18:18.258
It's the chapter where we read that Israel had been finally set free from the slavery in Egypt.

18:19.170 --> 18:29.365
And so you can only imagine the excitement in their minds, the anticipation in their step as they march their way outside of the land of Goshen to the place that the Lord guided them.

18:31.248 --> 18:37.878
This is truly one of the greatest miracles we see in the Word of God, maybe in the top five, at least for mine.

18:39.881 --> 18:46.290
Well, the message today is all about the small and simple part of what the Israelites were supposed to do.

18:47.746 --> 18:55.415
And for timeline purposes, this chapter is after Pharaoh, let the Israelites go after stubbornly, saying no to God.

18:56.776 --> 19:00.801
It took 10 plagues before he gave up his rule over them.

19:02.944 --> 19:05.567
Verse one, chapter 14, can you put it up, please?

19:07.609 --> 19:15.378
Then the Lord said to Moses, tell the Israelites to turn back and encap near high high wrath between Megdol and the sea.

19:15.874 --> 19:19.818
They are to encamp by the sea, directly opposite Baal Zephon.

19:20.659 --> 19:27.706
Pharaoh will think the Israelites are wandering around the land in confusion, hemmed in by the desert.

19:27.726 --> 19:30.809
I will harden Pharaoh's heart, and he will pursue them.

19:31.510 --> 19:34.973
But I will gain glory for myself through Pharaoh and all his army.

19:35.674 --> 19:38.917
And the Egyptians will know that I am the Lord.

19:40.359 --> 19:41.620
So the Israelites did this.

19:42.701 --> 19:43.762
When the king of Egypt

19:43.906 --> 19:50.734
was told that the people had fled Pharaoh and his officials changed their minds about them and said, what have we done?

19:51.816 --> 19:55.019
We have let the Israelites go and have lost their services.

19:57.362 --> 20:01.768
So he had his chariot made ready and took his army with him.

20:02.208 --> 20:07.575
He took 600 of the best chariots along with all the other chariots of Egypt.

20:08.316 --> 20:11.499
We're talking all hands on deck, all his big guns.

20:12.721 --> 20:13.682
With officers,

20:13.954 --> 20:15.275
over all of them.

20:18.138 --> 20:20.600
I'm going to take you to my first point, trust God's plan.

20:20.821 --> 20:21.561
So here we go.

20:23.123 --> 20:32.952
From Pharaoh's perspective, he's thinking everything's falling perfectly into place, that they could just grab them and bring them back and make them slaves again.

20:32.972 --> 20:43.442
And if they rebel, they will slaughter them right there and then, saying if they can't be my slaves, then they don't deserve to live.

20:44.322 --> 20:50.089
Likely he saw their wandering through the wilderness as a sign that God was not with them anymore.

20:51.370 --> 20:53.533
Israel was now trapped with nowhere to go.

20:53.553 --> 20:57.858
There was only the Vasi in front of them and only one way out.

20:58.539 --> 21:00.641
All fire we needed to do was box them in.

21:02.664 --> 21:09.171
See, the Israelites thought they were lured into a trap, but in God's eyes that trap was not for them.

21:10.273 --> 21:11.314
It was for their enemy.

21:12.642 --> 21:18.310
Now, why did God lead Israel to a dead end between a rock and a hard place?

21:18.731 --> 21:22.397
Or in this case, between a pharaoh and a Red Sea?

21:24.340 --> 21:32.091
We see that in verse 4, to reveal to Egypt that the God of Israel is the only true God.

21:34.194 --> 21:36.337
But all that people saw was just a dead end.

21:39.102 --> 21:42.066
You know, I've seen this over and over in my life.

21:42.370 --> 21:44.594
and have witnessed the same in the lives of others.

21:45.555 --> 21:46.016
That ends.

21:48.200 --> 21:52.527
You're in a pickle, you're stuck, and there's no way to get out.

21:53.689 --> 21:58.398
And then God's people begin to pray, and all of a sudden God makes a way.

22:01.483 --> 22:03.687
Can I see some hands if you've seen that in your life?

22:04.748 --> 22:05.650
Thank you, amen.

22:07.682 --> 22:12.370
I mean, you're thinking that there is no way on this planet that we can get out of this dead end.

22:13.471 --> 22:21.084
And all of a sudden, you humble yourself, you pray, you seek God the Lord, and He makes a way out of nowhere.

22:22.566 --> 22:23.268
And what does it do?

22:23.388 --> 22:26.152
It brings honor and glory to God.

22:27.014 --> 22:28.957
It reveals that He alone is God.

22:29.157 --> 22:29.698
I've seen it.

22:30.199 --> 22:31.581
I've heard it at this church.

22:32.382 --> 22:32.883
Miracles.

22:33.004 --> 22:34.546
And I love those miracles.

22:36.962 --> 22:38.845
continuing on on verse eight.

22:41.269 --> 22:48.680
The Lord hardened the heart of Pharaoh, King of Egypt, so that he pursued the Israelites, who were marching out boldly.

22:48.720 --> 23:02.802
The Egyptians, all Pharaoh's horses and chariots, horsemen and troops pursued the Israelites and overtook them as they camped near by the sea near Pi Hairoth, opposite Baal Zephon.

23:03.874 --> 23:08.700
A spare approach, the Israelites looked up and there were the Egyptians marching after them.

23:09.982 --> 23:13.646
They were terrified and cried out to the Lord.

23:14.968 --> 23:16.229
Did you catch that?

23:17.231 --> 23:21.135
In verse 8, it says, the Israelites were marching out boldly.

23:21.195 --> 23:29.606
And then just a couple of verses later on, verse 10, when they saw the Egyptians marching after them, they were terrified.

23:31.408 --> 23:33.010
What happened to their confidence?

23:34.306 --> 23:38.210
See, their trust was in their circumstances, not God.

23:39.572 --> 23:40.413
So what did they do?

23:40.453 --> 23:43.336
They went to the Lord and cried out to Him.

23:45.118 --> 23:52.166
Folks, this is the correct response when fear and worry and anxiety enter our minds and hearts.

23:52.947 --> 23:56.611
This should not be our second or last.

23:56.631 --> 23:58.654
This should be our first priority.

24:00.556 --> 24:02.418
You know, I can't really blame

24:02.530 --> 24:04.152
These were lights being afraid here.

24:04.953 --> 24:06.175
Put yourself in their place.

24:06.855 --> 24:12.162
There's the sea in front of you, a seemingly impossible massive body of water.

24:13.123 --> 24:16.487
There's no way to go in it without drowning or at least to their thought.

24:17.849 --> 24:28.782
And then behind you, there's an army of angry and ruthless Egyptian chariots with all its military technology bearing down upon you in a hurry.

24:30.244 --> 24:31.666
You're left with no options.

24:31.970 --> 24:36.656
There's no way out and it looks to all human appearances that you're going to get massacred.

24:38.819 --> 24:42.704
I don't blame a person for being afraid or even at least in this situation.

24:43.745 --> 24:45.888
They weren't afraid over nothing.

24:48.931 --> 24:52.356
Now I don't think we'll have anything like this happen to us, Lord forbid.

24:53.417 --> 25:00.466
But let's be honest, many of the things that we get all worked up in our Christian life are nothing in the scale of life

25:01.026 --> 25:02.808
and especially in the scale of eternity.

25:04.169 --> 25:18.665
There are small insignificant things and many times we just get bent out of shape and always thinking of the worst case scenario and so shaking in our walk with God over things that are essentially trivial.

25:20.568 --> 25:21.168
Have you done that?

25:21.569 --> 25:21.889
I have.

25:23.271 --> 25:30.098
Things that you thought would happen and we're talking about so far remote but never happens anyway.

25:31.714 --> 25:34.219
There are those cases and then there are serious matters.

25:35.882 --> 25:39.589
It matters not only for my life but for the lives of people around me.

25:40.090 --> 25:42.234
And it may even matter for the glory of God.

25:43.075 --> 25:48.465
Yes Lord, I'm alarm about this and that was the situation for Israel at this particular time.

25:49.888 --> 25:52.112
Crying out to God was the right thing to do.

25:54.417 --> 25:55.218
Verse 11.

25:57.698 --> 26:04.606
They said to Moses, was it because there were no graves in Egypt that you brought us to the desert and to die?

26:04.646 --> 26:10.792
What have you done to us by bringing us out into Egypt, out of Egypt?

26:11.433 --> 26:12.234
What were you thinking?

26:14.176 --> 26:16.979
That's not what it says in here, but you see, that was their tone.

26:18.381 --> 26:21.704
Didn't we say to you in Egypt, leave us alone.

26:21.764 --> 26:23.186
Let us serve the Egyptians.

26:24.354 --> 26:28.500
It would have been better for us to serve the Egyptians than to die here in the desert.

26:30.383 --> 26:30.764
Wow.

26:32.426 --> 26:33.668
Tell us what you really think.

26:34.970 --> 26:37.234
I didn't know they had sarcasm back then.

26:37.254 --> 26:46.888
They really thought Moses came up with this clever and evil plan to lead them all out in the wilderness so that they could all die.

26:48.230 --> 26:50.674
Now that's a conspiracy theory, isn't it?

26:52.738 --> 26:55.462
But I want two things I want you to see here.

26:56.784 --> 27:00.369
First, they disrespected God's appointed one.

27:01.009 --> 27:04.454
Second, they distorted the past.

27:06.597 --> 27:08.219
They respected God's appointed one.

27:08.239 --> 27:12.225
When things were not going their way, they wanted to put the blame on someone.

27:13.667 --> 27:15.569
But they don't want to put it ever on God.

27:15.670 --> 27:16.571
No, not at all.

27:17.592 --> 27:18.994
So who's next one in line?

27:19.815 --> 27:21.778
The person appointed by God.

27:22.370 --> 27:25.934
Moses was the next easy target and should take all the fault.

27:26.534 --> 27:27.055
Makes sense.

27:28.857 --> 27:30.078
Where was the loyalty?

27:31.379 --> 27:33.201
They were so quick to turn on him.

27:35.403 --> 27:42.351
You know, as I read this verses, it's so easy to think those Israelites were ridiculous, right?

27:43.872 --> 27:49.458
But may I ask, would you allow the word of God to be a mirror to your own self?

27:49.794 --> 27:55.924
and see how crazy it is for you and I or any of us to think the same thing as they did.

27:57.907 --> 28:05.139
Do we blame the appointed godly people he placed in our life when things are not going our way?

28:07.062 --> 28:13.192
Secondly, they distorted the past thinking it was better for them in Egypt than it really was.

28:14.855 --> 28:16.818
You know, we call it the good old days.

28:18.242 --> 28:22.567
You are romanticizing your past before Jesus Christ changed your life.

28:24.309 --> 28:30.015
By spiritual analogy, you're looking back to Egypt and you're thinking how wonderful it was.

28:31.476 --> 28:39.004
Folks, I will not trade a bad day with Christ to the hundred good days without Christ.

28:40.926 --> 28:44.370
The Lord freed us from the bondage of sin and death.

28:45.506 --> 28:52.794
May our circumstances, however bad they are, never tempt us to view our past as better than our future with God.

28:52.994 --> 28:53.214
Amen?

28:56.058 --> 29:00.022
Verse 13, Moses answered the people.

29:03.746 --> 29:07.931
Wait, after all we've been through, you're gonna talk to me like that?

29:10.533 --> 29:14.738
After all I've done for you, you're still questioning my intentions.

29:16.642 --> 29:17.363
You know, I'm done.

29:17.403 --> 29:19.165
Here's my stick.

29:19.706 --> 29:20.187
Go at it.

29:20.707 --> 29:21.128
Peace out.

29:21.629 --> 29:21.949
I'm done.

29:22.750 --> 29:23.411
Is that what he said?

29:25.353 --> 29:27.737
I was tempted to say that if I was there.

29:29.098 --> 29:29.959
But look what he says.

29:32.162 --> 29:33.544
Do not be afraid.

29:34.646 --> 29:39.832
Stand firm and you will see the deliverance that the Lord will bring you today.

29:41.294 --> 29:44.178
The Egyptians you see today, you will never see again.

29:44.514 --> 29:47.899
And here's the verse I underlined, highlighted, bolded, everything.

29:48.981 --> 29:50.704
The Lord will fight for you.

29:51.425 --> 29:54.890
You need only to be still.

29:56.473 --> 29:58.916
Simple, but yet profound, wasn't it?

30:00.098 --> 30:03.023
Which brings me to my next point, obey God's command.

30:04.565 --> 30:07.009
Notice that he didn't say, let's come up with a battle plan.

30:07.950 --> 30:10.855
He didn't say, everyone, grab a weapon and prepare to fight.

30:10.875 --> 30:12.818
That's what I would do.

30:13.378 --> 30:16.061
He didn't say, let's try to negotiate with Pharaoh.

30:16.081 --> 30:19.746
He said, stand firm and you will see what God will do.

30:21.188 --> 30:28.237
Folks, this is the heart of biblical faith, believing that God is working even when you can't see how.

30:29.378 --> 30:33.404
Trusting that God has a plan even when you can't understand it.

30:34.885 --> 30:38.270
The command to be still doesn't mean to be passive or inactive, no.

30:39.031 --> 30:41.554
It means to cease from your frantic efforts

30:41.890 --> 30:44.374
to solve the problem in your own strength.

30:45.395 --> 30:50.323
It means to stop trying to manipulate the situation to get the outcome you want.

30:51.745 --> 30:59.096
It means to quit attempting to force doors open that God has closed or to close doors that God has opened.

31:00.478 --> 31:04.644
When God says he will fight for you, he's not offering to be your help in battle.

31:05.465 --> 31:08.690
He's not volunteering to assist you with your strategy

31:09.538 --> 31:13.443
He's declaring that he is taking over the entire situation.

31:15.126 --> 31:18.130
He is assuming full responsibility for the outcome.

31:19.011 --> 31:21.214
He is guaranteeing victory.

31:22.756 --> 31:24.899
This is what happened at the Red Sea.

31:25.960 --> 31:29.025
God didn't give the Israelites better weapons to fight the Egyptians.

31:29.585 --> 31:29.806
No.

31:31.107 --> 31:33.431
He didn't teach some military tactics.

31:33.471 --> 31:35.954
He didn't even tell them to run or hide.

31:38.914 --> 31:41.858
Now I don't mean to spoil the story, but you know what God did?

31:42.639 --> 31:49.007
He simply opened an impossible path through the sea and then closed it on their enemies.

31:50.128 --> 31:50.969
They never thought of that.

31:51.089 --> 31:51.630
Nobody did.

31:54.694 --> 32:00.461
The same God who fought for Israel at the Red Sea is the same God who wants to fight for you today.

32:02.083 --> 32:07.250
The same power that part of the waters is available to part whatever standing in your way.

32:08.770 --> 32:15.698
And the same love that delivered them from slavery is working to deliver you from every bondage you have.

32:18.021 --> 32:21.044
You have to stop interfering with God's process.

32:21.425 --> 32:25.269
You have to quit trying to help him do what only he can do.

32:26.331 --> 32:31.677
You have to trust that his ways are higher than yours and his thoughts are higher than yours.

32:32.798 --> 32:35.922
This doesn't mean you become lazy or irresponsible.

32:36.290 --> 32:38.253
Being still doesn't mean you stop praying.

32:38.293 --> 32:40.997
You stop seeking God or stop walking in obedience.

32:41.658 --> 32:45.623
It means you stop trying to control outcomes that are beyond your control.

32:46.425 --> 32:49.569
It means to stop worrying about things that are in God's hands.

32:50.470 --> 32:52.093
It means you stop fighting battles.

32:53.495 --> 32:54.656
The God has already won.

32:54.697 --> 32:57.901
The promise is clear.

32:57.941 --> 32:59.544
The Lord will fight for you.

33:01.126 --> 33:04.050
Not might fight or could fight if you're good enough.

33:05.058 --> 33:08.062
Not will fight if you figure out the right formula.

33:09.584 --> 33:11.667
He will fight for you.

33:12.908 --> 33:14.390
This is his commitment.

33:14.510 --> 33:15.532
This is his commitment.

33:15.792 --> 33:19.056
His promise to every believer that who trusts in his name.

33:20.718 --> 33:32.914
Your job, my job, is to be still, to trust, to watch, to worship, to stand firm in faith while God moves heaven and earth on your behalf, amen?

33:37.634 --> 33:38.595
Do not be afraid.

33:40.418 --> 33:43.743
Stand firm and watch God will do.

33:45.004 --> 33:47.087
Do you know why some people miss the miracle?

33:49.310 --> 33:54.197
It's because they won't stand still and or try to work some miracle themselves.

33:55.840 --> 33:59.264
Folks, miracles can't happen without Christ, period.

34:00.947 --> 34:03.250
You might be able to conjure up some

34:03.458 --> 34:10.986
Some kind of answer to your problem, but that just means you're settling for mediocre instead of waiting for God's miracle.

34:13.830 --> 34:15.091
Sometimes we make it worse.

34:18.535 --> 34:23.060
You know, there was this story that Sylvia told in one of our Bible studies.

34:23.140 --> 34:25.062
And ladies, you might remember this more than I do.

34:25.122 --> 34:27.345
I forgot how the beginning went.

34:29.007 --> 34:32.050
But there was this person who went up to heaven

34:34.018 --> 34:38.484
God gave him this person a tour of one of the warehouse full of things.

34:40.106 --> 34:42.450
And this person asked, Lord, what are these?

34:43.792 --> 34:48.478
God says, these are all your missed miracles and unclaimed blessings.

34:50.521 --> 34:51.703
He goes, what are you talking about?

34:51.723 --> 34:52.103
That one?

34:53.185 --> 34:53.525
Oh, yeah.

34:54.967 --> 34:55.268
Remember?

34:55.748 --> 34:56.770
How come I didn't get that one?

34:57.651 --> 34:58.712
Well, you cried out to me.

34:58.772 --> 34:59.954
You wanted something else.

35:00.738 --> 35:02.120
Or how about that one, Lord?

35:02.200 --> 35:02.940
I didn't get that one.

35:03.021 --> 35:04.002
Why didn't I get that one?

35:04.742 --> 35:08.326
Well, because you want to settle on your own ideas.

35:09.648 --> 35:10.489
How about that one, Lord?

35:10.589 --> 35:12.191
I know I remember getting that one.

35:12.491 --> 35:13.272
How come it's in here?

35:14.173 --> 35:16.956
Well, Ellen, you're supposed to get double portions of that.

35:21.241 --> 35:26.066
But you cried out to me and you were convinced that yours was better than mine.

35:29.154 --> 35:32.639
Do you still want to settle for your own mediocre results?

35:33.420 --> 35:35.564
Or do you want God's finest miracles?

35:38.428 --> 35:43.115
Verse 15, then the Lord said to Moses, why are you crying out to me?

35:43.135 --> 35:44.998
Tell the Israelites to move on.

35:45.579 --> 35:52.910
Raise your staff and stretch out your hand over the sea to divide the water so that the Israelites can go through the sea on dry ground.

35:54.092 --> 35:58.258
I will harden the hearts of the Egyptians so that they will go in after them.

35:58.882 --> 36:03.708
I will gain glory through Pharaoh and all his army, through his chariots and his horsemen.

36:04.570 --> 36:13.682
The Egyptians will know that I am the Lord when I gain glory through Pharaoh, his chariots and his horsemen."

36:13.702 --> 36:16.706
My next point, believe God's timing.

36:18.749 --> 36:20.131
I love verse 15.

36:20.531 --> 36:22.974
God says, why do you cry out to me?

36:26.099 --> 36:28.722
And here's how this situation worked out in my mind.

36:28.802 --> 36:32.927
I can't really say this is exactly how it happened, but it seems to make sense to me.

36:33.989 --> 36:43.360
Moses boldly stands before the people, and he says to the people, don't be afraid, stand still and see the salvation of the Lord.

36:44.301 --> 36:50.249
Moses spoke just like a good leader should speak in front of his people, full of confidence, full of faith in God.

36:51.270 --> 36:53.593
And then Moses says, okay, give me a few minutes.

36:54.855 --> 36:57.458
And then he goes and gets on his knees before the Lord.

36:58.658 --> 37:00.461
Oh, would you do?

37:00.921 --> 37:02.043
Would you please do something?

37:02.404 --> 37:04.106
Oh, God, I don't know what you're going to do.

37:04.146 --> 37:10.296
He pours out his heart and prays for an outcome.

37:11.918 --> 37:12.960
And what does God say?

37:13.020 --> 37:16.225
God says, why are you crying out to me?

37:16.285 --> 37:17.427
Why are you still praying?

37:18.468 --> 37:20.131
Would you stop with the praying Moses?

37:21.192 --> 37:22.274
You need to get to work.

37:22.975 --> 37:23.956
It's time to move.

37:26.040 --> 37:27.602
I believe there's something

37:28.162 --> 37:30.205
powerful about this command.

37:30.225 --> 37:34.390
There's a time to pray and a time to act.

37:35.692 --> 37:37.575
It was not the time to get on your knees.

37:37.955 --> 37:41.120
It was time to move on your feet.

37:41.140 --> 37:45.325
You can pray along the way, but you need to get busy Moses because there's stuff to be done.

37:45.365 --> 37:51.794
There are some people who keep on praying when the Lord has already answered their prayer.

37:52.896 --> 37:54.738
He's just waiting for you to claim it.

37:58.242 --> 38:08.193
Verse 19, then the angel of God who had been traveling in front of Israel's army withdrew and went behind.

38:09.375 --> 38:16.022
The pillar of cloud also moved in front and stood behind him, coming between the armies of Egypt and Israel.

38:16.323 --> 38:21.829
Throughout the night, the cloud brought darkness to the one side and light to the other side.

38:22.610 --> 38:26.194
So neither went near the other all night long.

38:28.546 --> 38:33.232
which brings me to my last point, experience God's protection.

38:35.014 --> 38:44.506
These verses illustrate God's protective presence as the angel of God and pillar of cloud shift to safeguard the Israelites from the pursuing Egyptians.

38:45.427 --> 38:56.882
The angel of God moved from guiding Israel in the front to guarding them in the back, from pointing to protecting them, from acting as a guide

38:57.570 --> 38:58.791
to acting as a shield.

39:00.433 --> 39:06.859
I think we often have little idea how much God does to protect us against our unseen enemies.

39:08.260 --> 39:13.005
We should be very thankful every day for his unseen and divine protection.

39:14.346 --> 39:18.770
I couldn't even imagine that what our life would be like without it, his protection.

39:21.253 --> 39:26.738
You know what, for the sake of time, let me skip to verse 29, since we already know the end of the story.

39:28.034 --> 39:37.704
Verse 29, but the Israelites went through the sea on dry ground with a wall of water on their right and on their left.

39:38.264 --> 39:39.926
I wish I could have been there to see that.

39:40.486 --> 39:41.928
That must have been amazing.

39:44.450 --> 39:51.177
That day the Lord saved Israel from the hands of the Egyptians and Israel saw Egyptians lying dead on the shore.

39:52.318 --> 39:56.402
And when the Israelites saw the mighty hand of the Lord displayed against the Egyptians,

39:56.930 --> 40:02.998
the people feared the Lord and put their trust in him and then who?

40:03.959 --> 40:05.101
Moses is servant.

40:06.443 --> 40:07.304
What a great ending.

40:09.166 --> 40:16.055
You know, I heard from a preacher once that sending all those plagues to the Egyptians was not the difficult part.

40:16.356 --> 40:18.558
The parting of the Red Sea was the easy part.

40:19.720 --> 40:24.306
The hard part was the convincing and gaining of his children's trust.

40:26.178 --> 40:32.906
Look at what great lengths the Lord went to show His people to let them know how much He loves them.

40:37.752 --> 40:47.965
If there's someone here who hadn't given their lives to Christ, let me say this, Israel had been slaves for hundreds of years.

40:49.587 --> 40:52.831
No matter how hard they worked, they couldn't free themselves.

40:54.353 --> 40:55.474
Sin is the same way.

40:57.922 --> 41:02.608
No, it chases, it enslaves, it never lets go in its own.

41:03.930 --> 41:05.071
You cannot outrun it.

41:06.293 --> 41:11.599
You cannot defeat it by efforts, religion, or even your good intentions.

41:13.081 --> 41:14.503
That's why God made a way.

41:16.205 --> 41:21.572
Just like God opened the sea of Israel, he made a way to free us from sin.

41:22.994 --> 41:26.418
See, salvation is not about what you do.

41:26.690 --> 41:28.052
It's about what God does.

41:31.736 --> 41:34.239
The cross of Jesus is our Red Sea moment.

41:35.520 --> 41:45.693
And just like God defeated and destroyed Egyptian sin, lost its power, that lost its sting, and Satan lost his claim through Christ's death on the cross.

41:47.375 --> 41:53.682
What once enslaved us cannot follow us through salvation, but you have to make that leap of faith, my friend.

41:55.682 --> 42:01.571
Just like the Israelites had to step forward in faith, I need you to do the same.

42:02.772 --> 42:07.439
Trust God, step forward, and leave Egypt behind.

42:08.020 --> 42:08.301
Amen?

42:09.663 --> 42:10.564
Let's close in prayer.

42:12.387 --> 42:20.038
Heavenly Father, we come to you today feeling overwhelmed by the battles we're facing.

42:21.861 --> 42:25.586
Like the Israelites at the Red Sea, we feel trapped with no way out.

42:26.850 --> 42:29.233
We can't see how this situation will ever change.

42:30.514 --> 42:32.076
Our flesh wants to panic.

42:33.618 --> 42:34.960
Our mind wants to worry.

42:35.581 --> 42:40.446
Our heart wants to take control of the circumstances that are beyond us.

42:42.289 --> 42:47.515
Lord, we confess that we've been fighting battles that belong to you.

42:48.416 --> 42:53.502
We've been trying to solve problems in our own strength that require you.

42:55.084 --> 42:56.786
We have been carrying burdens

42:57.378 --> 42:59.381
that you never intended us to bear.

43:01.103 --> 43:06.310
We have been worrying about outcomes that are completely in your hands.

43:07.151 --> 43:13.039
Forgive us for trying to be our own God instead of trusting you as our Lord and Savior.

43:16.824 --> 43:24.434
Help us to be still and know that you are the only and true God, amen.

